I have successfully implemented all the frontend components and E2E tests as specified in the design. Here's a summary of what was created:

## Summary

### New Pages Created

1. **`/quotas`** - Cost Tracking & Quota Management
   - Organization overview with total pages, costs, and active users
   - User quotas table with usage progress bars and status indicators
   - Edit quota modal for adjusting page limits and overage actions
   - Cost history table with period breakdowns

2. **`/policies`** - Print Policy Engine
   - Policy cards showing priority, status, and conditions/actions
   - Create/Edit policy modal with conditions (max pages, approval required) and actions (force duplex, grayscale, etc.)
   - Toggle enable/disable for policies
   - Delete policies functionality

3. **`/audit-logs`** - Advanced Audit Logging
   - Searchable and filterable audit log table
   - Filter by type (User, Printer, Job, Organization, Auth)
   - Color-coded action badges (create=green, delete=red, update=amber, auth=blue)
   - Export to CSV functionality
   - Pagination support

4. **`/email-to-print`** - Email-to-Print Configuration
   - Configuration status card showing enabled state, email address, default printer
   - Edit modal with settings for allowed senders, max attachments, auto-release, approval requirements
   - Recent email print jobs table with status badges
   - Test email functionality

5. **`/print-release`** - Secure Print Release
   - Release station with printer selector and PIN input
   - Pending jobs list with document details and metadata
   - Release and cancel buttons for each job
   - Auto-refresh (polling) for new jobs

### API Service Methods Added

- `quotasApi` - getUserQuota, getOrgQuotas, updateQuota, getPeriods
- `policiesApi` - list, get, create, update, delete, toggle, reorder
- `printReleaseApi` - createSecureJob, getPendingReleases, releaseJob, cancelRelease
- `emailToPrintApi` - getConfig, updateConfig, getJobs, testEmail

### E2E Tests Created

- `e2e/tests/quotas.spec.ts` - 10 test cases for quota management
- `e2e/tests/policies.spec.ts` - 11 test cases for policy engine
- `e2e/tests/audit-logs.spec.ts` - 14 test cases for audit logs
- `e2e/tests/email-to-print.spec.ts` - 16 test cases for email-to-print
- `e2e/tests/print-release.spec.ts` - 15 test cases for print release

All TypeScript type checks pass successfully.
